      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t really know how googlesource sets the committer timestamp, but at least with a local git, it\u0027s possible to override the time using the GIT_COMMITTER_DATE environment variable. According to \u0027git help log\u0027, git will not return hashes in strictly chronological order if that would cause them to be out of logical order.\n\nThat\u0027s a long way of saying you should be aware that there\u0027s some chance that \"sort.Sort(gitHashSlice(gitHashes))\" does not order the commits the same way that \u0027git log\u0027 does.",
